{"questionId":"9066296","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Both vinegar (a dilute aqueous solution of ethanoic acid) and bleach are used as cleaning agents.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Bleach reacts with ammonia, also used as a cleaning agent, to produce the poisonous compound chloramine, NH<sub>2</sub>Cl.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Draw a Lewis (electron dot) structure of chloramine.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/5965/5ci.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"133\" height=\"101\"> &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>[<span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">✔]</span></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><strong>Note</strong>:&nbsp;Accept any combination of dots/crosses or lines to represent electron pairs.</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9066296","referenceCode":"19M.2.hl.TZ1.5c(i)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Draw a Lewis (electron dot) structure of chloramine.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c(i)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 4: Chemical bonding and structure","4.3 Covalent structures","Core","Topic 4: Chemical bonding and structure"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}